  <steps>
    <step num="0">Dice the onion. </step>
    <step num="1">Cut the broccoli into florets. </step>
    <step num="2">Dice the sweet potato. </step>
    <step num="3">Add the water, broccoli, chickpeas, sweet potato, onion, quinoa, garlic, ginger, red pepper flakes, turmeric, tamari, salt, tomatoes, and coconut milk to a slow cooker. Stir to combine. </step>
    <step num="4">Cover and cook for 4 hours on high or 8 hours on low, until the sweet potato is tender and the curry has thickened. </step>
    <step num="5">Serve warm over rice. Garnish with parsley, if desired. </step>
    <step num="6">Enjoy! </step>
